descCRN['10146&TermDescription=Fall%202017'] = '<p>Notes:<br />*Cross-listed with BIOL 351-01; first day attendance required*<br/>A study of biological processes at the molecular level with an emphasis on the chemistry of biological molecules, physical biochemistry, structure of proteins, mechanisms and kinetics of enzyme catalyzed reactions, and introduction to intermediary metabolism, including the metabolism of carbohydrates and lipids. Three lecture hours and one three-hour laboratory per week. (4 credits)</p>';
