descCRN['10483&TermDescription=Fall%202017'] = '<p>Notes:<br />*First day attendance required; ACTC students may register on April 28th with permission of instructor*<br/>This course introduces the field of computer science, including central concepts such as the design and implementation of algorithms and programs, testing and analyzing programs, the representation of information within the computer, and the role of abstraction and metaphor in computer science. The exploration of these central ideas will draw examples from a range of application areas including multimedia processing, robotics, turtle graphics, and text processing.  Course work will use the Python programming language. (4 credits)</p>';
